The paper deals with a geometric problem of connecting points and labels with non-intersecting rectilinear paths, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves finding crossing-free layouts, which is related to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DS and cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for maximizing the number of labeled sites and minimizing the total leader length, which are optimization problems (cs.GT). Finally, the use of algorithms and computational techniques to solve the problem suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational science (cs.SI).
